<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: April 27, 2026</p>

        <h2>1. Overview</h2>
        <p>Postiz is a self-hosted social media scheduling application. This privacy policy explains how we handle your data when you use Postiz with Facebook integration.</p>

        <h2>2. What Data We Collect</h2>
        <p>When you connect Postiz to Facebook, we collect:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Your Facebook Page ID</li>
            <li>Permission to publish content on your behalf</li>
            <li>Your Facebook Page name and basic information</li>
            <li>Content you schedule for posting</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p>Your data is used solely for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Scheduling and publishing content to your Facebook pages</li>
            <li>Displaying your pages and posts in Postiz dashboard</li>
            <li>Authenticating your Facebook account</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data Storage</h2>
        <p>All data is stored locally on your self-hosted Postiz instance. Your data is not stored on external servers. You have complete control over your data and can delete it at any time by disconnecting Facebook or uninstalling Postiz.</p>

        <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>We do not share, sell, rent, or distribute your data to any third parties. Your data is only shared with Facebook when you authorize Postiz to post on your behalf. This sharing is controlled by your Facebook account permissions.</p>

        <h2>6. Security</h2>
        <p>Postiz stores your Facebook access tokens securely in your self-hosted instance. We recommend:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Using HTTPS for your Postiz instance</li>
            <li>Keeping your server updated</li>
            <li>Using strong passwords for your Postiz account</li>
            <li>Regularly backing up your data</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Access your data stored in Postiz</li>
            <li>Delete your data by disconnecting Facebook</li>
            <li>Disconnect your Facebook account at any time</li>
            <li>Export your data if supported by your Postiz instance</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Third Party Services</h2>
        <p>Postiz integrates with Facebook. When you use Facebook integration, Facebook's privacy policy also applies. Please review Facebook's privacy policy at https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/</p>

        <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this privacy policy occasionally. Changes will be effective immediately upon posting to this page.</p>

        <h2>10. Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy or your data privacy, please contact your Postiz administrator or the person who manages your Postiz instance.</p>

        <hr style="margin-top: 40px; border: none; border-top: 1px solid #ddd;">
        <p style="font-size: 12px; color: #7f8c8d; margin-top: 20px;">
            This is a basic privacy policy for Postiz self-hosted instances. Please ensure it complies with your local laws and regulations. If you use Postiz in the EU, please ensure GDPR compliance. If you target users under 13, ensure COPPA compliance.
        </p>
